news.title: Panchkula civic body plan to replace 18,500 street lights delayed by two months
news.para: In May, the MC had taken out a tender on the orders of the department of urban local bodies (ULB) that had included Panchkula in cluster-I. Yamunanagar, Ambala, Kurukshetra and Karnal were the other cities in the cluster that would be getting new street lights.

news.title: Mumbai cops to own BDD service quarters under new rule
news.para: The Mumbai police commissionerate that owns 2,900 tenements in the BDD chawls stands to lose 1,800 of them on redevelopment due to a decision to allow families of policemen occupying the bulk of the service quarters to get permanent ownership after redevelopment.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM's advisor urges officials to fast track land survey
news.para: Kallam, chairman of the state-level steering and implementation committee for the comprehensive survey, said that chief minister Y S Jagan Mohan Reddy is closely monitoring its progress.

news.title: Karnataka to soon have integrated townships in all industrial hubs
news.para: After reviewing his department, Nirani told reporters that the industries department had decided to prepare a blueprint on residential townships in industrial areas that would come up in future across the state.

news.title: Budget homes pushed to Hyderabad's fringes as land prices hit the roof
news.para: ​Their new locations: Kollur, Kismatpur, Shamshabad among others. On the eastern corridor, the budget destinations have shifted to areas along the Nagarjuna Sagar Road – about 30 km from the Secunderabad Railway Station.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body to file criminal cases against those involved in illegal construction
news.para: Activists, on the other hand, reiterated that several illegal structures have come up mostly in Ghansoli ward. In sector 21, new illegal shopping units have come up despite media highlighting this issue in the recent past.

news.title: Gurugram: 10 structures in illegal colony razed in Sector 72A
news.para: Officials said, the builder — NKV developers — did not comply with the orders despite FIR being filed against them in June 2019 and two demolition drives being carried out in February and July 2020.

news.title: Chennai: Pallavaram, Avadi residents can pay property tax online soon
news.para: When implemented, online services will bring a relief to lakhs of residents who live in areas governed by smaller local bodies like Avadi corporation, Pallavaram municipality, Tambaram municipality, Sriperumbudur town panchayat and others.

news.title: McKinsey & Co leases 45,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai's BKC
news.para: The total tenure of the lease will be five years, implying a total rental of nearly Rs 100 crore, said people aware of the matter.

news.title: AAR ruling making office refurbishing costs eligible for tax credit may lead to litigations
news.para: As of now, only the cost that contributes towards the output of a company — raw materials, input services, machinery, etc. — are eligible for input tax credit.

news.title: Gurugram: GPL Eden Heights' residents say developer violated norms
news.para: They have sought a structural inspection of the society by the department of town and country planning (DTCP), alleging that the conditions of the completion certificate have not been fully complied with by the developer.

news.title: Soon, a drive to recover Rs 400 crore dues from builders in Noida
news.para: Various government agencies, including the UP-Rera, the Noida Authority and the Greater Noida Authority, have already issued recovery certificates against these developers after having failed to recover dues from them.

news.title: Discharge plea of DHFL rejected in cheating case in Mumbai
news.para: ​The court said that while the representative appointed by the monitoring committee is discharged, the company would be prosecuted through the Wadhawan brothers who, it said, were responsible for conduct of its business.

news.title: US: Landlords look for an exit amid federal eviction moratorium
news.para: Most evictions for unpaid rent have been halted since the early days of the pandemic and there are now more than 15 million people living in households that owe as much as $20 billion in back rent, according to the Aspen Institute.

news.title: China Evergrande vows to resolve debt risks after regulators' warning
news.para: Financial markets are worried that any crisis at Evergrande could ripple through China's banking system as the company struggles to find the cash it needs to pay its many lenders and suppliers.
